	     Harare - Zimbabwe's military shortly will address the nation on state-run television. The military's role has been questioned after its leaders sat by while longtime President Robert Mugabe defied calls to resign during a speech Sunday night. The military has had Mugabe under house arrest for several days. Mugabe has called a Cabinet meeting Tuesday morning, while the ruling party will begin the process of impeaching him when Parliament resumes the same day.    24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  